Portfolio Analytics - Installation & Configuration Guide

Overview
This document explains how to install and configure the Portfolio Analytics project on Windows, macOS, and Linux.

Prerequisites (All Operating Systems)
- Node.js (LTS recommended)
- npm (comes with Node.js)
- Git (optional, if cloning from GitHub)

Obtain the Code
Option A: From a ZIP
1) Extract the ZIP file to a local folder.

Option B: From GitHub (optional)
1) Clone the repository:
   git clone <repository-url>
2) Change into the project directory:
   cd <project-directory>

Environment Configuration
Create a file named .env in the project root and add the following values:
VITE_AUTH0_DOMAIN=dev-13oyn2a5bk3vnp6q.us.auth0.com
VITE_AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=tycPIChY3ozWjJpvJDoWflNEyWevmMFO
VITE_AUTH0_AUDIENCE=https://dev-13oyn2a5bk3vnp6q.us.auth0.com/api/v2/
VITE_AUTH0_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173

Install Dependencies
From the project root directory, run:
   npm install

Run the Application (Development)
Start the development server:
   npm run dev

Once running, open your browser and navigate to the local URL printed in the terminal (typically http://localhost:5173).

Notes
- No additional external services or credentials are required beyond the .env values above.
- If npm is not recognized, ensure Node.js is installed and your PATH is updated.
